-- White House urges GM, workers to negotiate
-- 
-- Mon Sep 24, 2007 2:27pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/24/us-gm-uaw-strike-bush-idUSWAT00813820070924

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The White House on Monday urged General Motors Corp. to negotiate after the United Auto Workers declared a strike against the company. 

 "We encourage both the company and the UAW to continue to work through their differences," White House spokesman Tony Fratto said.